A convicted sex offender has gone missing from an open prison. People are warned to not approach Gary Butcher, 55, who absconded from HMP North Sea Camp in Boston, Lincolnshire. The criminal, who is serving a life sentence for aggravated burglary, was reported missing just after 5.30am on Tuesday. He is described as a white male with a stocky build, with brown/grey hair and blue eyes. Butcher has a swallow tattoo on his right arm and a ‘Phillip-Trina’ tattoo on his left arm. Police say he may have travelled to the Leicestershire area. Senior Investigating Officer, Detective Inspector Paul Coleman said: ‘If you have any information to his current whereabouts, please contact us immediately. ‘If you do see him, please do not approach him and instead, call us on 101 quoting incident 37 of 31st May and if it’s an emergency, dial 999.’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.